Paramedics say the man was found in his vehicle with a gunshot wound to his head. JOHANNESBURG - A man has been shot and wounded in Benoni in the East Rand.Paramedics say the man was found in his vehicle with a gunshot wound to his head; he s been airlifted to the Charlotte Maxeke Academic Hospital.ER24 s Russel Meiring said: While we were treating the patient, paramedics found that his vital signs rapidly deteriorated. Advanced life support interventions were immediately initiated in an effort to stabilise his vital signs, once treated the man was then airlifted by a private medical helicopter to the Charlotte Maxeke Hospital for urgent treatment. Police are investigating the circumstances around the shooting.